561
00:35:15,250 --> 00:35:17,540
Then you can use it for me then.

562
00:35:17,540 --> 00:35:20,610
It's not like I'm calling you "cute" or anything.

563
00:35:21,500 --> 00:35:23,920
I'd say you're "Tay" (Cool/Handsome) instead.

564
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:26,810
What did you say?

565
00:35:26,810 --> 00:35:30,320
I'd say you're "Tay" instead.

566
00:35:36,120 --> 00:35:38,030
If a shortie like me is "Tay,"

567
00:35:38,030 --> 00:35:41,960
then someone tall like you can be "cute" for me, too.

568
00:35:46,760 --> 00:35:51,100
If I'm willing to be cute in your eyes.

569
00:35:51,100 --> 00:35:54,160
You'll be "Tay" only for my eyes, right?

570
00:36:10,230 --> 00:36:11,870
Let's go inside the house, Ai Koon Chai.

571
00:36:11,870 --> 00:36:12,560
Okay.

572
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:14,700
Before I can't stop myself and kiss you, right here.

573
00:36:14,700 --> 00:36:16,140
Okay.

574
00:36:23,010 --> 00:36:26,640
Ae, which flower do you think is pretty?

575
00:36:26,640 --> 00:36:28,360
It already looks nice on the plant.

576
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:30,010
Why would you cut them?

577
00:36:30,010 --> 00:36:34,470
I... put roses in a vase for my mom's birthday every year.

578
00:36:43,010 --> 00:36:45,700
So, why does it have to be roses?

579
00:36:47,063 --> 00:36:49,001
When I was very young,

580
00:36:49,001 --> 00:36:53,400
a big bouquet of roses was always delivered on her birthday every year.

581
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:56,480
So I asked her who sent them to her.

582
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:59,920
Mom said that dad sent them.

583
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:04,130
At that time, I thought that my dad loved my mom very much.

584
00:37:04,130 --> 00:37:09,323
But I also wondered why didn't dad just deliver them himself.

585
00:37:09,323 --> 00:37:14,893
Until I realized that... the one who sent them was my dad's secretary.

586
00:37:18,190 --> 00:37:21,095
What flowers are these? They're so beautiful.

587
00:37:21,095 --> 00:37:23,444
They are roses.

588
00:37:23,444 --> 00:37:25,944
Your dad sent them to mom.

589
00:37:27,160 --> 00:37:28,950
Do you like them?

590
00:37:45,670 --> 00:37:47,230
It's something strange.

591
00:37:47,230 --> 00:37:52,450
Because presently, that secretary is my father's new wife.

592
00:37:56,159 --> 00:37:58,759
He never remembered our faces, Ae.

593
00:37:59,459 --> 00:38:02,289
He never remembered my mother's birthday at all.

594
00:38:05,037 --> 00:38:10,197
Once dad and mom got divorced, there were no roses sent over ever again.

595
00:38:12,120 --> 00:38:16,400
So I decided to pick roses for my mom.

596
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:20,050
At that time, my hands were covered in wounds.

597
00:38:20,050 --> 00:38:23,760
Some roses looked nice, others were not so much.

598
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:25,940
And I also told my mom that...

599
00:38:25,940 --> 00:38:30,340
From now on, I'll be the one who gives you roses every year.

600
00:38:31,340 --> 00:38:33,320
Thank you, dear.

601
00:38:35,120 --> 00:38:38,920
Oh, my!!! Does it hurt, son?

602
00:38:41,230 --> 00:38:43,270
Thank you so much.

603
00:39:04,920 --> 00:39:07,360
If you can make your mother happy,

604
00:39:07,360 --> 00:39:10,130
then I will be the one to make you happy.

605
00:39:15,530 --> 00:39:18,320
So, which flower do you want?

606
00:39:18,320 --> 00:39:19,740
I'll cut them for you.

607
00:39:19,740 --> 00:39:21,310
This one.

608
00:39:25,780 --> 00:39:30,050
♫ I won’t wish to catch those distant stars ♫

609
00:39:30,050 --> 00:39:34,330
♫ I don’t want to make them mine ♫

610
00:39:34,330 --> 00:39:38,600
♫ I won’t wish for the world to keep spinning ♫

611
00:39:38,600 --> 00:39:44,020
♫ I won’t turn back time ♫

612
00:39:44,020 --> 00:39:48,860
♫ In this universe, there is nothing more meaningful ♫

613
00:39:48,860 --> 00:39:51,910
♫ Than you whom I am longing for ♫

614
00:39:51,910 --> 00:39:56,310
♫ I only beg for you to be with me forever ♫

615
00:39:56,310 --> 00:40:00,000
♫ You're the only one I'm asking for ♫

616
00:40:00,560 --> 00:40:04,320
♫ I want you to be my sky when I fly ♫

617
00:40:04,320 --> 00:40:09,640
♫ Be my guiding star when I'm lost ♫

618
00:40:11,610 --> 00:40:13,500
- Hello.
- Hello, Ae

619
00:40:13,500 --> 00:40:16,310
I'm so sorry. I just had some important work come up.

620
00:40:16,310 --> 00:40:20,270
