644
00:42:02,010 --> 00:42:03,660
Yes.

645
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:06,300
So, have you met each other before?

646
00:42:06,300 --> 00:42:10,910
This is Ae, dear. He's Pete's friend from university.

647
00:42:10,910 --> 00:42:12,660
Hello.

648
00:42:13,230 --> 00:42:17,020
Ae, DeLi has been my friend since we were little kids.

649
00:42:17,020 --> 00:42:18,680
Hello.

650
00:42:19,520 --> 00:42:23,690
Then I'll leave you kids to chat for first. I'll excuse myself for now, all right?

651
00:42:23,690 --> 00:42:26,040
- Sure.
- Okay, Mother.

652
00:42:30,540 --> 00:42:33,570
That's very nice to be able to be at the same university as Pete, too.

653
00:42:33,570 --> 00:42:35,160
Actually, I wanted to study there, too.

654
00:42:35,160 --> 00:42:36,760
But my dad wouldn't let me.

655
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:39,830
He said that I had to study at the same place he did no matter what.

656
00:42:39,830 --> 00:42:42,210
Such a shame. Right, Pete?

657
00:42:44,340 --> 00:42:45,800
Pete?

658
00:42:45,800 --> 00:42:49,340
Yeah, it's such a shame that we don't see each other very much.

659
00:42:49,340 --> 00:42:51,008
True.

660
00:42:51,008 --> 00:42:54,788
Then... should we meet more often then?

661
00:43:01,220 --> 00:43:06,030
[Preview]

662
00:43:06,030 --> 00:43:08,220
Pete, you know how to peel shrimp now?

663
00:43:08,220 --> 00:43:10,940
